# Repository Structure

**Project**: WebRTC Engineering — demos and projects repository

> **Single Source of Truth**: [docs/01-repository-structure.md](../../docs/01-repository-structure.md)

## Quick Summary

- **`src/01_fundamentals/` … `src/05_architecture/`**: Numbered concept modules (`NN_lesson/` inside each).
- **`src/06_demos/NN_name/`**: Incremental runnable WebRTC labs (`01_getusermedia/`, …).
- **`src/07_experiments/NN_name/`**: Measurements and spikes (`01_stun_vs_turn/`, …).
- **`src/08_projects/NN_name/`**: Integrated applications (`01_video_call/`, …).
- **`src/types/`, `src/utilities/`**: Shared code — **not** numbered.
- **`docs/`, `tools/`, `assets/`**: Support trees — **not** numbered (no lesson sequence).
- **`.archive/`**: Legacy content; leave unless Swamy asks to migrate.

Do not list internal-only paths in public-facing docs.
